r you are going to learn goodness and compassion from them, or use them to destroy your environment.', 2874, 0), (56174, 'We the humans are too tiny to know something so grand as an Eternal Driving Force behind the Universe. Ultimately what would really matter in the development of our species as a whole is, we the humans serving humanity.', 2874, 0), (56175, 'When you move to a new environment with cultural and social characteristics different from your own, it is only logical, that you loosen some of the knots of your religious doctrines, to embrace the new and vivid environment as much as you wish to be embraced by the environment.', 2874, 0), (56176, 'Nothing looked the same, and everything looked the same.', 5669, 0), (56177, 'Jacob being sensitive is an endowment. Think about all you''d miss out on if you didn''t feel things so deeply, or see things so clearly." "But feeling good things deeply means you feel bad things deeply, too." "Would you rather walk around oblivious to the meaning of things hidden under the surface and the opportunities to feel wonder and joy? Would you want to miss out on moments that take your breath away?', 5669, 0), (56178, 'I am merely an insignificant creature on a microscopic blue dot in the vastness of space.', 2874, 0), (56179, 'Sometimes the solution of a problem is just the perspective of thinking.', 12389, 0), (56180, 'Most people in life follow!We follow the things, the people or the strict rules to achieve something in our lives. And there is a blessing when life hinders one to follow these things and slows the speed of following others and sometimes giving us no way to do so. Then you realize what lies in your inner self, the hidden treasure. The moment you become master of your hidden treasure, the world follows you and not you.', 12389, 0), (56181, 'Don''t lead enthusiasm out of your life! Else life won''t lead you anywhere.', 12389, 0), (56182, 'Love if mishandled spreads hatred and creates agony and chaos.', 12389, 0), (56183, 'to spoil in the borrowed time of denial is a liar to its self. and yourself, to banish the seeds of time is fruitful to be honest to one’s self.', 12697, 0), (56184, 'The concern of your brain is not to see the actual nature of reality, but to represent the reality to you in such a way that suits your needs.', 2874, 0), (56185, 'I don''t believe in luck, but rather destiny. And destiny comes when you chase opportunity, only then will you make your own path in life.', 6385, 0), (56186, 'the only true path to your dream is to perceive what others dim illogical', 12698, 0), (56187, 'What melody will our rivers remember if songbirds forget how to sing?', 12699, 0), (56188, 'All the repressed emotions and subconscious desires in time lead to some kind of psychological or physiological breakdown, if kept unchecked.', 2874, 0), (56189, 'Look for reasons to be happy, and soon you will find many!', 12154, 0), (56190, 'Misery teaches you more than joy.', 2874, 0), (56191, 'We only have one chance in this life, so don''t waste it on trivial people and matters.', 11007, 0), (56192, 'Pleasure and Pain participate equally in moulding character.', 2874, 0), (56193, 'Denial of the Self accomplishes nothing.', 2874, 0), (56194, 'Words can mean nothing, or be daggers in someone''s heart. Choose them wisely.', 12700, 0), (56195, 'The Bible is not religion, nor are the Vedas. The Torah is not religion, nor is the Quran, or any other scripture on earth.', 2874, 0), (56196, 'The most formidable adversary of evil is a persistent man with a loud conscience.', 12410, 0), (56197, 'Once you reach the brink of your will power, you have two options - either give up, or keep going. That decision decides whether you''ll reach your goal.', 2874, 0), (56198, 'My experience of that liberation, what Buddha had called Nirvana, set me off in the path of scientific investigation of that Oneness, the thing people call, meeting with God. And that meeting triggered an unquenchable thirst in me to