INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (56301, 'The divinity you seek is born with you.', 2874, 0), (56302, 'Realization of your inner divinity is the scientific religion of thinking humanity.', 2874, 0), (56303, 'Sometimes life appears one way, but what matters is how you internalize life and its lessons.', 11011, 0), (56304, 'Where does your soul walk? Does it walk in the sunlit woods or hide in the shadowy forest?', 7602, 0), (56305, 'Parents rarely let go of their children, so children let go of them. They move on. They move away. The moments that used to define them - a mother''s approval, a father''s nod - are covered by moments of their own accomplishments. It is not until much later, as the skin sags and the heart weakens, that children understand; their stories, and all their accomplishments, sit atop the stories of their mothers and fathers, stones upon stones, beneath the waters of their lives', 131, 0), (56306, 'GOD in not just in the details, He is the detail.', 5028, 0), (56307, 'When life gives you lemons, you don''t make lemonade. That''s for pantywaisters. No. You pucker up, suck them dry, then throw the used rinds back in life''s face with a giant fuck-you and a gesture for more.', 12723, 0), (56308, 'Your worst battle is between what you know and what you feel!', 12114, 0), (56309, 'If you don''t get the wrong people out of your life, you will never be able to get the right people in it!', 12114, 0), (56310, 'There are some moments you won''t completely heal from, those rare ones you will take torn open to the grave but throughout all the big moments that shake you up there will be countless tiny experiences that help you laugh all over again.', 3305, 0), (56311, 'This whole life is an art of knowing when to sit and when to stand up!', 3701, 0), (56312, 'You really don''t want to be his/her first love. They need to have first fallen in love with Jesus.', 5028, 0), (56313, 'Forgiveness is the subjective and fertile ground the acorn falls upon when gifted to ourselves and others.', 5777, 0), (56314, 'Sometimes people forget the bridge that connected them to success.', 12143, 0), (56315, 'Our evolution depends on our memory. If we keep forgetting the mistakes of the past, only to keep repeating them, then we will never change. Humanity will never move forward, spiritually or morally, to become superior beings.', 2678, 0), (56316, 'Fight for what you want out of this one life.', 918, 0), (56317, 'Stop chasing society’s definition of success and chase your own definition of success. Success is an emotion that is experienced when you are completely fulfilled and content with where you are in life; it has nothing to do with a specific job, a specific amount of money in your bank account, or the quality of material possessions you acquire. You can be the richest man in the world, but still, feel unsuccessful, and you can be the poorest man in the world, but still, feel extremely successful.', 12724, 0), (56318, 'Who needs toothpaste when you have cigarettes?', 12725, 0), (56319, 'I help people achieve their dreams.', 5043, 0), (56320, 'We believe in the good old days; we believe our best is in the past. Our past is our memories, our past is our learnings, our past should stay where it is. And we should let it.', 8446, 0), (56321, 'You will meet people in life who will just dislike you for no reason, not because there is anything wrong with you but because everything is going right for you. Until they master their own peace, they will always try to destroy yours.', 6378, 0), (56322, 'When there is nothing left to love for, it''s easy to die for something.', 12726, 0), (56323, 'The material world coexists alongside the ideal life, and the purest intentions are bound to the earth by ridiculous threads, but they are threads of iron and they are not easily broken.', 12727, 0), (56324, 'What differentiates brother most from brother and beast is neither purpose, perspective nor prowess. It is simply intent.', 12726, 0), (56325, 'Life is war. By implication, life in itself places humanity with the need for battle in the struggle for success', 12728, 0), (56326, 'Don’t accept a life that has been molded for you by others because eventually you’ll succumb to its falseness.', 12729, 0), (56327, 'Don''t cling to a mistake, just because you spent so much time making it.', 12730, 0), (56328, 'Influence is when you don''t talk and yet your words fill the room when you are absent and yet your presence is felt everywhere. ', 5028, 0), (56329, 'I will form good habits and become their slave.', 1369, 0), (56330, 'It is better to leave a child well instructed than to hand over the whole world in the hands of a fool', 12728, 0), (56331, 'We cannot change the past. We can only take action in the present and, therefore, change the future.', 5043, 0), (56332, 'Learn to grow with what each season brings.', 11678, 0), (56333, 'Let the love not escape from within.', 12731, 0), (56334, 'When you compete, you gain more than you lose, even when you lose.', 6385, 0), (56335, 'We only have one life and two choices: sadness and regret for a past we cannot change or happiness for every moment we can choose how to live.', 12732, 0), (56336, 'When they slam a door on your face, it''s life, adding another 110 lb plate to your bar and telling you: "Let''s see how strong you are".', 12732, 0), (56337, 'In every moment of our life, we can deactivate the self-destruction command.', 12732, 0), (56338, 'Daily life is an ongoing adaptation process of imprinting our memory’s storage center with useful data and the ceaseless expurgation of undesirable facts, exfoliation of destructive thoughts, and weeding out annoying emotional quirks that seemingly sprout out of thin air.', 2764, 0), (56339, 'Nowadays, nobody can teach you a useful thing about life, since models are outdated one moment after.', 12732, 0), (56340, 'Fly’ GenerationWe stand tall, we stand proud, we are the ‘fly’ generationWe think what we learn to think and dream with our eyes openWe keep our hearts on our sleeves for it to be brokenbut we can take it, we are the ‘fly’ generation.We question things when we need to understandIts important we know, how it works, where we standWhy all this pain and no explanation?we need answers, we are the ‘fly’ generation.We love to hate and hate to love, what have we become?Since when is that the norm? when did we succumb?The victims will be forgotten and culprits will change faceBut we will still be running, running to win the invisible race.So here’s to the untold stories and six degrees of separationwe can take it, after all… we are the ‘fly’ generation.', 2891, 0), (56341, 'We Neuroscientists have come a long way in proving that God is neither a Delusion nor an Almighty Being watching over life on Earth. God is the Event Horizon of Human Consciousness. I termed this state of attaining God, as ''Absolute Unity Qualia''.', 2874, 0), (56342, 'There is no such thing as Hardcore Philosophy or Hardcore Science. Real Science and Real Philosophy do not destroy each other, they simply fulfil and enrich each other.', 2874, 0), (56343, 'The negative thoughts inside my head blown into a multiple rays of hope for my goals in life adding some motivated aspects of my ambition triggered my inner sanctum to prolong the basic human emotions. ', 12733, 0), (56344, 'Age is only a number. Maturity to a large extent is dependent on your exposure to life, its experiences and your lessons from them.', 11024, 0), (56345, 'It is imperative you stay in touch with your inner self so you don’t lose the essence of who you truly are.', 11024, 0), (56346, 'The impact of your life will go beyond your imagination. Live your life to be a blessing.', 5028, 0), (56347, 'I found myself when I least expected you- at the same old rocking chair in the room with the same flavor of tea. The only difference was the tea had turned cold, just as life had. And I found myself with an option. I could abandon this tea anytime and make a fresh one. You see?', 12734, 0), (56348, 'I''ve learned a lot this year...I''ve learned that some people will wrong you, forgive them anyway.I''ve learned that things might not work out as you thought they should, do them anyway.But what struck me the most isno matter how good or bad things are, life goes on, so live it anyway.', 12735, 0), (56349, 'Truth, at times is just an accepted opinion', 12736, 0), (56350, 'Sometimes life ask you a question, but you couldn''t find answer in any book. You have to create answer yourself.', 12737, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (56351, 'Are we living life, or is life living us?', 9743, 0), (56352, 'Comfortable? Don''t be. I believe in those moments where we grow comfortable is where we stop growing, and in order to keep evolving, God slips the rug from beneath our feet and makes us look up.', 12738, 0), (56353, 'Every day you have to be open to like things you’ve never liked before. Every day you have to realize you can’t get too comfortable.', 12739, 0), (56354, 'We must look at things with new eyes.Work to live. To enjoy the life we have now and prepare for our lives to come. Not live to work, which is to eternally be a slave to a process of task to provide us with basic sustenance for a continued pitiful existence!I strive to live and love not simply survive and endure', 5162, 0), (56355, 'Our media is a WHORE', 5162, 0), (56356, 'After a TimeAfter a time, all losses are the same.One more thing lost is one thing less to lose;And we go stripped at last the way we came.Though we shall probe, time and again, our shame,Who lack the wit to keep or to refuse,After a time, all losses are the same.No wit, no luck can beat a losing game;Good fortune is a reassuring ruse:And we go stripped at last the way we came.Rage as we will for what we think to claim,Nothing so much as this bare thought subdues:After a time, all losses are the same.The sense of treachery--the want, the blame--Goes in the end, whether or not we choose,And we go stripped at last the way we came.So we, who would go raging, will go tameWhen what we have we can no longer use:After a time, all losses are the same;And we go stripped at last the way we came.', 12740, 0), (56357, 'Virtues untie the knots that life could sometimes bring our way and they glide us through easily.', 11024, 0), (56358, 'So many people from my past taught me that it''s not everyone that''s in my life wants to see me achieve my goals and be great, but I thank God they''re no longer in my life because I moved on a long time ago, welcome to my present.', 11055, 0), (56359, 'You Are Reaching A Tank using a ladder and by the time you get into the tank someone pulls off your ladder.This is what life is.', 12741, 0), (56360, 'Life may be circular but its circumference keeps getting wider for us to grow.', 7502, 0), (56361, 'Sometimes, we become afraid to change because others judgment and opinions. Then, we making puerile excuses to please others, not ourselves.', 12742, 0), (56362, 'In the end we all come to be cured of our sentiments. Those whom life does not cure, death will. The world is quite ruthless in selecting between the dream and the reality even where we will not. Between the wish and the thing, the world lies waiting.', 548, 0), (56363, 'Don''t let someone else''s opinion of you become your reality. No matter what you going through don''t give up.', 8450, 0), (56364, 'Look forward, not behind. "Your best days are still out in front of you." Be focus & keep your dreams ALIVE', 8450, 0), (56365, 'This caterpillar does not just simply grow wingsFirst, it must alter its mind; transform the very being of itselfIt must climb the tallest tree, the highest mountainSwim the deepest of oceansWalk through the fiercest of flamesAnd then, if it chooses, this caterpillar can become a butterfly', 12743, 0), (56366, 'If you want to make room for something new, you must let go of something old that no longer serves you.', 187, 0), (56367, 'There are two powerful fuels, two forces; motivation and inspiration. To be motivated you need to know what your motives are. Over time - and to sustain you through it - your motivation must become an inner energy; a ''motor'' driving you forward, passionately, purposefully, wisely and compassionately... come what may, every day. Inspiration is an outer - worldly - energy that you breathe and draw in. It may come from many places, faces, spaces and stages - right across the ages. It is where nature, spirit, science, mind and time meet, dance, play and speak. It keeps you outward facing and life embracing. But you must be open-minded and open-hearted to first let it in and then let it out again. Together - blended, combined and re-entwined - motivation and inspiration bring connectivity, productivity, creativity and boundless possibilities that is not just ''self'' serving but enriching to all humanity and societies...just as it should be.', 4889, 0), (56368, 'Sharpen and trust your judgement: learn when spending is a shrewd investment and when it is merely an indulgence', 4889, 0), (56369, 'During my life journey I''ve discovered an interesting thing once you stop seeking outside you discover what already resides within. ', 4889, 0), (56370, 'Some people just carry heavy hearts and more often than not it has nothing to do with you.', 3305, 0), (56371, 'Seeds eat no mudStem eats no seed,Leaf eats no stem,Flower consumes no leafNor fruit eats flower,The fruit, quit the tree with happinessWithout harming it.But the intelligent human-being, eats up all; still unhappy , hungry and ...', 12744, 0), (56372, 'We have a saying in the desert: It is better to see the truth, than to imagine it.', 12745, 0), (56373, 'The team that keeps winning is not the most talented but the most hard-working.', 12746, 0), (56374, 'Humility is not an attribute but a key to development.', 12746, 0), (56375, 'The waves of changes propel advancement.', 12746, 0), (56376, 'Happiness is, when it comes to the understanding of its meaning, to sometimes be unhappy.', 11043, 0), (56377, 'I''m on a missionWinning Novel / Screenplay written in HollywoodGoogle for updated info', 12747, 0), (56378, 'To be fearless, you must simply fear less.', 5028, 0), (56379, 'Goals want to realize themselves.', 12746, 0), (56380, 'You only think women are inferior when your own mother is failure.', 12748, 0), (56381, 'If I stress about a goal, I won''t remember to find the way to get there.', 12746, 0), (56382, 'You be good. That''s your business. The rest, leave to God. That''s his business.', 4618, 0), (56383, 'My imaginary pal up there, Mr. NOT, tells me it''s my dog-damn ism to kick your illusory he-man''s ass. Now, what do you say to that?', 4618, 0), (56384, 'LIFE LESSONSIf you plant honesty, you will reap trust* If you plant goodness, you will reap friends* If you plant humility, you will reap greatness* If you plant perseverance, you will reap contentment* If you plant consideration, you will reap perspective* If you plant hard work, you will reap success* If you plant forgiveness, you will reap reconciliation* If you plant faith in God, you will reap a harvestSo, be careful what you plant now; it will determine what you will reap later.', 12749, 0), (56385, 'The road to overcoming your fears could lead you to unbearable places but sometimes such gives you an edge than nothing else could give.', 5089, 0), (56386, 'Focus on living your life, and let the opinions of others be what they are.', 12750, 0), (56387, 'A LIE is BEAUTIFUL, melodious, STYLISH, and attractive. On the contrary, TRUTH is UGLY, rude, DULL and repulsive. That''s why often people get attracted towards LIES. They embrace it and live with. The truth is usually ignored and disowned.', 12638, 0), (56388, 'They say copying is a form of flattery, I say it''s lack of originality.', 12751, 0), (56389, 'I am a living breathing word of GOD.', 5028, 0), (56390, 'We Burmese,'' he began, ''are experts at looking for what''s not there. It''s something you should learn to do too. You must look for what''s missing and learn how to find the truth in these absences.', 12752, 0), (56391, 'The only thing that will make you successful is the believe you have in yourself', 11685, 0), (56392, 'Time is priceless; you are responsible for your time. Earn it or kill it, your choice', 11685, 0), (56393, 'I cry even harder, thinking of how it could have been, of how I thought it would be. For the first time, I want to give up, to die, because suddenly everything is