 your highest priority, and plan time to work on them.', 3800, 0), (57834, 'Turn down things that are in consistence with your priorities.', 3800, 0), (57835, 'It is no use setting priorities if you won’t stick to them.', 3800, 0), (57836, 'If you really want to be an effective time manager, you will have to learn to say no to other people and do so frequently.', 3800, 0), (57837, 'Schedule time for focused effort.', 3800, 0), (57838, 'The best way to effectively use time is to schedule it.', 3800, 0), (57839, 'Whatever you have chosen to be your priority, set a time to it and be focused on achieving it.', 3800, 0), (57840, 'Be always employed to something useful.', 3800, 0), (57841, 'Always improve on things you do better and faster.', 3800, 0), (57842, 'People who have become great like Benjamin Franklin only became great because they learned how to invest time into improving whatever it is they were called to do..', 3800, 0), (57843, 'In order to gain mastery over whatever you have been called to do, you must look for ways of improving how you do them.', 3800, 0), (57844, 'Greatness is born out of proper time management.', 3800, 0), (57845, 'Most people do not know how to exchange their lives for external treasures.', 3800, 0), (57846, 'In order to become great, one must understand the secret of time conversion.', 3800, 0), (57847, 'The only instrument through which time could be converted to yield greatness is the instrumentality of work.', 3800, 0), (57848, 'If you will exchange your life for greatness, if you will use the currency of time to buy greatness; then greatness will deliver to you every other thing you need in life.', 3800, 0), (57849, 'If there is anything you need in life that you haven’t gotten, it is because you are yet to pay for it via the currency of time.', 3800, 0), (57850, 'You can have anything you need in life, the only price you have to pay is for you to exchange your life for greatness and greatness will deliver that thing you need to y